The following amounts of Rob protein were used : lane 1 , none ; lane 2 , 0.5 ng ; lane 3 , 1 ng ; lane 4 , 2 ng ; lane 5 , 4 ng ; and lane 6 , 8 ng .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7896685" target="_blank">7896685</a>]<br></label>
<input id="act_similarity_39", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>The following amounts of Rob protein were used : lane 1 , none ; lane 2 , 4 ng ; lane 3 , 8 ng ; lane 4 , 12 ng ; lane 5 , 16 ng ; lane 6 , 20 ng ; and lane 7 , 30 ng FIG. 4 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7896685" target="_blank">7896685</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>The amountof shifted R-ori as a function of total R-ori in the presence of a constant amount of Rob protein ( Fig. 5 ) indicated that 16 pmol of protein was capable of shifting 2.7 pmol of R-ori , a ratioof Rob to oriC of about 6 to 1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8449900" target="_blank">8449900</a>]<br></li>
<li>The othaern,ovel33.14-kDa protein reported solubilized material yielded a more slowly migrating , shifted here , binds the right border of oriC and is named Rob .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8449900" target="_blank">8449900</a>]<br></li>
<li>The Rob protein is constitutively expressed and binds to the right arm of the E. coli origin of chromosome replication ( oriC ) , but its function is still unknown ( 46 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11741843" target="_blank">11741843</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both fusions terminate at position 3176145 , which is 91 bp downstream of the marbox , and both were signiﬁcantly activated by agents known to activate marA and soxS transcription or Rob function ( salicylate , paraquat and DIP respectively ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18673442" target="_blank">18673442</a>]<br></li>
<li>Two-tailed t tests were used to determine the significance of differences in the effects of the mutations on transcriptional activation as described previously .12 Wild-type and mutant Rob proteins were expressed from pBAD-his6-Rob and purified by nickel affinity chromatography utilizing the BioLogic DuoFlow protein purification system ( Bio-Rad ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22465792" target="_blank">22465792</a>]<br></li>
<li>What remains to be tested is whether constitutive Rob contributes to the basal expression of genes known to be induced by Rob overexpression , namely , fumC , sodA , and inaA ( 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626315" target="_blank">8626315</a>]<br></li>
<li>When A600 of the cultures reached 0.1 -- 0.2 , Rob expression in half of them was induced with 0.2 % arabinose and the other half was uninduced .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22465792" target="_blank">22465792</a>]<br></li>
<li>Baker , P. J. , Britton , K. L. , Rice , D. W. , Rob , A. & Stillman , T. J. ( 1992 ) J. Mol .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9346310" target="_blank">9346310</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our analysis revealed that inaA , marRAB , aslB , ybaO , mdlA , yfhD , and ybiS were transcriptionally activated by constitutive levels of Rob , while galT expression was repressed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10850996" target="_blank">10850996</a>]<br></li>
<li>One gene , galT , was repressed by Rob .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10850996" target="_blank">10850996</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this study , galT was the only gene repressed by Rob .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10850996" target="_blank">10850996</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since it is estimated that E. coli contains 5,000 molecules of Rob under normal conditions ( 42 ) , why this is sufﬁcient to activate mar and inaA but not other regulon promoters is unclear .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9393706" target="_blank">9393706</a>]<br></li>
<li>Rob binds at a very high afﬁnity to the promoters of the mar -- sox regulon apparently in the absence of low-molecular-weight effectors ( Kwon et al. , 2000 ) and activates the transcription of these genes in vitro ( Jair et al. , 1996 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12791142" target="_blank">12791142</a>]<br></li>
<li>The results ( Fig. 4 ) showed that Rob bound to acrAB promoter DNA at high afﬁnity even in the absence of any putative effector , and that the presence of 0.1 mM chenodeoxycholate did not alter the interaction between Rob and the target DNA in a manner that can be detected by this assay .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12791142" target="_blank">12791142</a>]<br></li>
<li>To identify genes regulated by Rob , we screened a library of random lacZ transcriptional fusions ( generated by MudJ ) for differential expression in the presence and absence of Rob .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10850996" target="_blank">10850996</a>]<br></li>
<li>Mixtures of the test and gnd reference promoters were transcribed under standard conditions in the absence and the presence of puriﬁed Rob protein ( 2 pmol ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626315" target="_blank">8626315</a>]<br></li>
<li>For the marbox transversion mutants ( no. 7 and 8 ) which are insensitive to stimulation by Rob , the presence of Rob increases the transcription of the chromosomal marRAB promoter and therefore only increases the repression of the mutant fusions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9393706" target="_blank">9393706</a>]<br></li>
<li>Notably , in the presence of Rob , Fis had a positive effect on mar transcription , unlike the situation in its absence , in which Fis weakly reduced transcription ( Table 4 and summarized in Table 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9393706" target="_blank">9393706</a>]<br></li>
