<li>However , Lon of E. coli also degrades speciﬁc substrates , such as cell-division inhibitor SulA ( Mizusawa and Gottesman , 1983 ) , transcriptional activators MarA , SoxS and Rob ( Griffith et al. , 2004 ; 2009 ) , idling ribosomal proteins ( Kuroda et al. , 2001 ) and antitoxins encoded by toxin-antitoxin modules ( Gerdes and Maisonneuve , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25491382" target="_blank">25491382</a>]<br></li>
<li>First , three independently regulated but homologous proteins , MarA , SoxS and Rob , activate a common set of promoters which results in multiple antibiotic resistance , superoxide resistance and organic solvent tolerance ( for review , see Alekshun and Levy , 1997 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10564485" target="_blank">10564485</a>]<br></li>
